# Trivy ignore list — consumed by the `Image Scan` CI job.
#
# Entries here are CVE IDs that the scanner would otherwise surface as
# CRITICAL or HIGH. Every entry must justify *why* it's accepted and how
# we'll get rid of it. Review this file each time the alpine base image
# is bumped — most entries should age out on their own.
#
# Format (one per line):
#   CVE-XXXX-YYYY  # short reason + expiry / exit condition

# musl in alpine:3.23 is 1.2.5-r21 on Docker Hub. Upstream advisory lists
# the fix in 1.2.5-r23 but alpine hasn't rebuilt the 3.23 tag with the
# patch yet (verified 2026-04-14: Docker Hub digest for alpine:3.23 is
# unchanged since 2026-01-28 and still ships r21). Remove this entry once
# the alpine:3.23 digest is refreshed upstream — tracked via #87
# (Renovate dockerfile pinDigests gap).
CVE-2026-40200  # musl CVE — alpine:3.23 not yet rebuilt with 1.2.5-r23

# zlib 1.3.1-r2 in alpine:3.23. Same situation as CVE-2026-40200 — fix
# exists in 1.3.2-r0 but alpine hasn't rebuilt the 3.23 tag yet. Remove
# when the alpine:3.23 base digest is refreshed upstream (#87).
CVE-2026-22184  # zlib CVE — alpine:3.23 not yet rebuilt with 1.3.2-r0
